tafsir[6]{c,v,t}:
  93,1,"Allah takes an oath on the beginning of the day."
  93,2,"And He takes an oath on the night when it darkens and people cease to move in it."
  93,10,"And do not rebuke the needy beggar."
  94,2,"And I have removed sin from you."
  94,3,"That which was burdening you to the extent that it almost broke your back."
  94,8,"And divert your passion and resolve towards Allah alone."